In [ ]:
def examiner(model, input, expected_output):
    sauce = {}
    predicted = []
    for k in input:
        predicted.append(model.predict(k.reshape(1,-1)))
    sauce["balanced_accuracy"] = balanced_accuracy_score(expected_output, predicted)
    sauce["confusion_matrix"] = confusion_matrix(expected_output, predicted)
    sauce["f1_score"] = f1_score(expected_output, predicted)
    sauce["recall_score"] = recall_score(expected_output, predicted)
    sauce["accuracy_score"] = accuracy_score(expected_output, predicted)
    sauce["percision_score"] = precision_score(expected_output, predicted)
    return sauce
